s of brothers Job and Samuel Stiles"},{"type":"parallel_descent","related_id":"HD1063","link_text":"Nathaniel Eggleston Hooker","display_label":"Both Hooker descendants died in Waterville Lucas County Ohio"}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"migration","header":"Migrated to Waterville Lucas County Ohio","body":"Hylas Stiles was born in Windsor CT (1793, same day-of-year as his sister Laura), grew up through the family's Enfield CT period, and migrated to Waterville in Lucas County, Ohio at some point before his 1871 death. The migration places him in the Connecticut-to-Ohio settlement pattern that brought several Hooker descendants westward — his second cousin Leonard Tuttle settled in Medina County Ohio by 1836, his first cousin Henry Stiles also died in Ohio, and Hooker descendant Nathaniel Eggleston Hooker died in the same Waterville OH fifteen years after Hylas."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"One of three Stiles cousins to migrate Ohio","body":"Hylas Stiles was one of three Esther Hooker Stiles descendants to migrate to Ohio in the same generation. His first cousin Henry Stiles(son of his uncle Samuel) also died in Ohio. His second cousin Leonard Tuttle(grandson of his great-aunt Keziah Stiles via Kezia Munson Tuttle) settled in Medina County Ohio by 1836."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Edward Hooker, Descendants of Rev. Thomas Hooker (1909), entry 1206"},{"label":"Henry Reed Stiles, The Stiles Family in America (1895), entry 416"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"hylas-stiles-1793"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}